</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
In the MNCN there are three lots labelled ' 
<taxonomicName authority="Scopoli, 1777" authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1777" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bulimus aristaceus" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="aristaceus">Bulimus aristaceus</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Crosse’">Crosse'</normalizedToken>
which were previously considered as syntypes. These lots appeared not to be conspecific, and only lot MNCN 15.05/7180 is considered as type material of this taxon. This species was recently re-described and re-figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="85 - 93" title="A snail in the long tail: a new Plekocheilus species collected by the ' Comision Cientifica del Pacifico' (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Amphibulimidae)." url="10.3897/zookeys.516.10228" volume="516" year="2015">Breure and Araujo (2015)</bibRefCitation>
. The figure of 
<bibRefCitation author="Crosse, H" journalOrPublisher="Journal de Conchyliologie" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="97 - 109" title="Descriptions des especes nouvelles." volume="18" year="1870">Crosse (1870)</bibRefCitation>
does not entirely adequately represent the current state of the shell as the colour marks largely have faded away.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
